MOORE v. WARDEN OF THE MARYLAND PENITENTIARY [App. No. 119,

September Term, 1965.]

Decided June 6, 1966.

Before Hammond, Marbury, OppEnheimER, Barnes and McWileiams, JJ.

Per Curiam.

Application for leave to appeal from a denial of post conviction relief is denied for the reasons set out in the opinion of Judge Jones in the court below.

Application denied.
